{
  "message": "test(fuzz): add corpus seeds and zone key manifest fuzz target\n\nCorpus seeds for existing fuzz targets:\n\nfcpc_frame/ (9 files):\n- empty.bin: Empty input edge case\n- just_magic.bin: Truncated after magic bytes\n- truncated_20.bin: Partial header\n- valid_empty.bin: Valid frame with empty payload\n- valid_16byte.bin: Valid frame with 16-byte payload\n- bad_magic.bin: Invalid magic number\n- bad_version.bin: Unsupported version field\n- dos_max_len.bin: Maximum length field to test DoS resistance\n- length_mismatch.bin: Declared length doesn't match actual\n\nfcps_datagram/ (2 files):\n- empty.bin: Empty input edge case\n- dos_max_source_id.bin: Maximum source ID to test parsing limits\n\nfcps_frame/:\n- Corpus files for FCPS frame parsing\n\nzone_key_manifest/:\n- Corpus files for zone key manifest parsing\n\nNew fuzz target:\nzone_key_manifest.rs (~2.8KB):\n- Fuzz target for ZoneKeyManifest CBOR parsing\n- Tests manifest validation and key extraction\n- Includes property-based invariant checks\n- Designed to find parsing panics and logic errors\n\nThese corpus seeds accelerate fuzzing by providing known interesting\ninputs that exercise edge cases, error paths, and boundary conditions.\nThe seeds were derived from protocol specifications and known attack\npatterns.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.5 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
